{"id":"810532312697683968","type":"text","timestamp":1772983849,"post_url":"https://www.tumblr.com/blog/view/goodtransgirl/810532312697683968","is_reblog":true,"added_content":true,"tags":[],"reblog_ready":true,"body":"<p><a href=\"https://notthegrouch.tumblr.com/post/712398700200296448/mentalhealthmemez-anarchistmemecollective\" class=\"tumblr_blog\">notthegrouch</a>:</p>\n\n<blockquote><p><a href=\"https://mentalhealthmemez.tumblr.com/post/690595453903011840/anarchistmemecollective-jasminesapphiresmany\" class=\"tumblr_blog\">mentalhealthmemez</a>:</p><blockquote><p><a href=\"https://anarchistmemecollective.tumblr.com/post/690580082367004672/jasminesapphiresmany-people-seem-to-think-it\" class=\"tumblr_blog\">anarchistmemecollective</a>:</p>\n\n<blockquote><p><a href=\"https://jasminesapphires.tumblr.com/post/682603705002082304/many-people-seem-to-think-it-foolish-even\" class=\"tumblr_blog\">jasminesapphires</a>:</p><blockquote><blockquote>“Many people seem to think it foolish, even superstitious, to believe that the world could still change for the better. And it is true that in winter it is sometimes so bitingly cold that one is tempted to say, ‘What do I care if there is a summer; its warmth is no help to me now.’ Yes, evil often seems to surpass good. But then, in spite of us, and without our permission, there comes at last an end to the bitter frosts. One morning the wind turns, and there is a thaw. And so I must still have hope.”</blockquote> <p>— Vincent Van Gogh</p></blockquote>\n\n\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-height=\"418\" data-orig-width=\"666\"><img src=\"https://64.media.tumblr.com/726eb36a2e8ef6e5d190cffa9ee9faf1/cae3b48b28810e46-90/s2048x3072/3629cc4375d03344165f22a99b4a6439df3394b4.png\" data-orig-height=\"418\" data-orig-width=\"666\" data-media-key=\"726eb36a2e8ef6e5d190cffa9ee9faf1:cae3b48b28810e46-90\" alt='meme of a person looking extremely excited and surprised with caption \"vincent van gogh?\"'/></figure></blockquote>\n\n\n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-height=\"176\" data-orig-width=\"750\"><img src=\"https://64.media.tumblr.com/4229fff34d4e0069f9ccbfd80ff65c2b/81a3058792cde14b-42/s2048x3072/d1fb82fbf0a64950dd1f3338e5204c2e9a3d1d83.jpg\" data-orig-height=\"176\" data-orig-width=\"750\" data-media-key=\"4229fff34d4e0069f9ccbfd80ff65c2b:81a3058792cde14b-42\"/></figure></blockquote>\n<blockquote><p>\n“If I am worth anything later, I am worth \nsomething now. For wheat is wheat, even if people think it is a grass in\n the beginning.” </p></blockquote><p>- Vincent van Gogh<br/></p></blockquote>\n\n\n<p>&ldquo;For wheat is wheat, even if people think it is a grass in the beginning.&rdquo;</p><p>This just in, Vincent van Gogh says Trans Rights!</p>","trail":[{"blog":{"name":"jasminesapphires","active":true,"theme":{"avatar_shape":"circle","background_color":"#FFFFFF","body_font":"Helvetica Neue","header_bounds":"","header_image":"https://assets.tumblr.com/images/default_header/optica_pattern_05.png?_v=671444c5f47705cce40d8aefd23df3b1","header_image_focused":"https://assets.tumblr.com/images/default_header/optica_pattern_05_focused_v3.png?_v=671444c5f47705cce40d8aefd23df3b1","header_image_poster":"","header_image_scaled":"https://assets.tumblr.com/images/default_header/optica_pattern_05_focused_v3.png?_v=671444c5f47705cce40d8aefd23df3b1","header_stretch":true,"link_color":"#00B8FF","show_avatar":true,"show_description":true,"show_header_image":true,"show_title":true,"title_color":"#000000","title_font":"Gibson","title_font_weight":"bold"},"share_likes":false,"share_following":false,"can_be_followed":true},"post":{"id":"682603705002082304"},"content_raw":"<p><blockquote>“Many people seem to think it foolish, even superstitious, to believe that the world could still change for the better. And it is true that in winter it is sometimes so bitingly cold that one is tempted to say, ‘What do I care if there is a summer; its warmth is no help to me now.’ Yes, evil often seems to surpass good. But then, in spite of us, and without our permission, there comes at last an end to the bitter frosts. One morning the wind turns, and there is a thaw. And so I must still have hope.”</blockquote> <p>— Vincent Van Gogh</p></p>","content":"<p><blockquote><p>&ldquo;Many people seem to think it foolish, even superstitious, to believe that the world could still change for the better. And it is true that in winter it is sometimes so bitingly cold that one is tempted to say, &lsquo;What do I care if there is a summer; its warmth is no help to me now.&rsquo; Yes, evil often seems to surpass good. But then, in spite of us, and without our permission, there comes at last an end to the bitter frosts. One morning the wind turns, and there is a thaw. And so I must still have hope.&rdquo;</p></blockquote> <p>&mdash; Vincent Van Gogh</p></p>"},{"blog":{"name":"anarchistmemecollective","active":false,"theme":[],"share_likes":false,"share_following":false,"can_be_followed":false},"post":{"id":"690580082367004672"},"content_raw":"<p><figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-height=\"418\" data-orig-width=\"666\"><img src=\"https://64.media.tumblr.com/726eb36a2e8ef6e5d190cffa9ee9faf1/cae3b48b28810e46-90/s2048x3072/3629cc4375d03344165f22a99b4a6439df3394b4.png\" data-orig-height=\"418\" data-orig-width=\"666\" data-media-key=\"726eb36a2e8ef6e5d190cffa9ee9faf1:cae3b48b28810e46-90\" alt='meme of a person looking extremely excited and surprised with caption \"vincent van gogh?\"'></figure></p>","content":"<p><figure class=\"tmblr-full\"><img src=\"https://64.media.tumblr.com/726eb36a2e8ef6e5d190cffa9ee9faf1/cae3b48b28810e46-90/s2048x3072/3629cc4375d03344165f22a99b4a6439df3394b4.png\" alt=\"meme of a person looking extremely excited and surprised with caption &quot;vincent van gogh?&quot;\" class=\"\"/></figure></p>"},{"blog":{"name":"mentalhealthmemez","active":false,"theme":[],"share_likes":false,"share_following":false,"can_be_followed":false},"post":{"id":"690595453903011840"},"content_raw"